text=(:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!PracticeCategory]]%0a%0a!Connotations of Words in a Language %0a%0a:Author: sgangu%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aHow do certain words come to bear their specific connotations? %0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aAs a result of the BLM movement, the large majority of us developed heightened awareness about the language we use to others and how that may affect them. We started to go over our every day words and consider the origins of these words and whether or not they have a place in our inclusive communities. For example, Github thought about renaming their master branch and people try to not refer to the master bedroom of a house as such. The reason is that the word "master" was used in America during times of slavery to place the white slave owners at a higher level. %0a%0aThis can only be one of many examples of how a seemingly arbitrary word came to bear a greater significance. I've noticed many other words in Telugu and English mean something simple but have strong connotations. For example, the color blue is just a color but it is also used to represent a negative, sad feeling. In Telugu, people say that someone "got off the red bus" to indicate that they aren't very knowledgable. This is because the buses that go from the villages to the cities are red in color. %0a%0aI want to understand how connotations behind the words we use actually develop. This is important to understand because words only seem to have the meaning and the power that we assign them. %0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a%0a%0a%0a(:section: :)%0a(:Category: PracticeCategory:)
